2026-03-22T14:29:58.402Z JOY-0024 item.created "Roadmap with adjusted line length" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:34:49.991Z JOY-0025 item.created "Multiline comment details in event log cause board panic" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:34:56.407Z JOY-0025 comment.added "Fixed: three-part fix. (1) append_event() now escapes newlines (\\n) and backslashes (\\\\) in the details field before writing, keeping the log strictly one-entry-per-line. (2) parse_log_line() rejects lines that do not start with a digit (fast path) and validates the timestamp is ISO 8601 before returning a LogEntry. Added unescape_details() for reading escaped content back. (3) board.rs uses .get(..10) instead of [..10] for defensive timestamp extraction. Migrated all 6 affected log files (umbrella + joy subproject) to escaped format. Added 4 new tests: escape_roundtrip, multiline_details_roundtrip, reject_non_timestamp_lines, timestamp_validation. Documented error output conventions in ADR-015." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:34:58.805Z JOY-0025 item.status_changed "new -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:42:32.601Z JOY-001C comment.added "Plan: Add joy ai check subcommand. (1) Compute SHA-256 hashes of the three embedded templates (instructions.md, setup.md, SKILL.md) at compile time via include_str\\!. (2) At runtime, hash the installed files in .joy/ai/ and compare. (3) If all match: print 'Up to date.' and exit 0. (4) If any differ or missing: run the existing copy_templates() logic to update, print what changed, and exit 2 so the AI tool can detect and reload. (5) Add instruction to AI templates: run joy ai check at session start." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:42:35.311Z JOY-001C item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:53:14.777Z JOY-001C comment.added "[x] joy ai check compares installed .joy/ai/ templates against embedded versions via SHA-256. Exit 0 = up to date, exit 2 = outdated with list and hint to run joy ai setup. [x] joy ai setup now uses the same diff logic: only writes changed templates, shows up to date / updated per file. [x] instructions.md and SKILL.md updated: joy ai check is now step 1 of session start." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:53:17.181Z JOY-001C item.status_changed "in-progress -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:55:59.818Z JOY-0024 comment.added "Plan: Both tree renderers (print_tree_node for parent grouping, print_ms_tree_node for milestone grouping) print titles without terminal width awareness. truncate_title() already exists in ls.rs but is only used in print_table(). Fix: compute available title space as terminal_width minus prefix_width minus metadata brackets (ID + [type] + [status] + [prio]) and truncate the title. Same approach for both active and inactive items." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:56:02.349Z JOY-0024 item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:57:19.072Z JOY-0024 comment.added "[x] Both tree renderers (print_tree_node, print_ms_tree_node) now truncate titles based on terminal width. Shared tree_title_width() computes available space by subtracting prefix, connector, ID, and metadata brackets from terminal width. Uses existing truncate_title() with '...' suffix. Works in both emoji and no-emoji modes." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:57:19.080Z JOY-0024 item.status_changed "in-progress -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T14:59:22.147Z JOY-0024 comment.added "[x] Follow-up fix: bracket width calculation was off by 1 per bracket (counted 2 chars for ' [X]' instead of 3). Also applies to joy ls --tree, not just roadmap." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T15:24:32.039Z JOY-0023 comment.added "Plan: (1) Create .joy/hooks/commit-msg hook that validates commit messages contain at least one item ID matching the project acronym (from project.yaml). Pattern: ACRONYM-XXXX (hex). (2) Merge commits are exempt (detect via MERGE_HEAD). (3) Error output follows ADR-015 rustc diagnostic format, including a note about --no-verify with audit policy warning. (4) joy init in onboarding mode (project already exists) sets core.hooksPath to .joy/hooks and prints setup confirmation. (5) Hook script is versioniert in .joy/hooks/ so it distributes via git. (6) Document in CONTRIBUTING.md: every commit must reference an item, subprojects need their own items (model A). (7) Update AI instructions: when working across umbrella and subprojects, create items in each affected project." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T15:35:52.450Z JOY-0023 comment.added "Plan update: (1) Hook and CI both accept two valid patterns: item ID (ACRONYM-XXXX) or [no-item] tag. No --no-verify recommendation. (2) [no-item] is the documented bypass, visible in git history, auditable. (3) Hook error message points to [no-item] instead of --no-verify. (4) just lint-commits uses the same logic. (5) GitHub/GitLab/Gitea Actions: defer to separate item. The CI recipe (just lint-commits) will need a wrapper per platform (GitHub Action, GitLab CI job, Gitea Action) since each has different PR/MR branch semantics." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T15:35:52.458Z JOY-0023 item.status_changed "new -> in-progress" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-22T15:40:00.436Z JOY-0023 comment.added "[x] commit-msg hook in .joy/hooks/ validates item ID (ACRONYM-XXXX) or [no-item] tag. Merge commits exempt. Error output in ADR-015 format. [x] joy init onboarding mode: detects existing project, installs hook and sets core.hooksPath. Idempotent on re-run. [x] just lint-commits checks all commits in a branch range (default main..HEAD), same logic as hook. Ready for CI integration. [x] CONTRIBUTING.md updated with item-per-commit policy and multi-repo rules. [x] AI instructions updated. Note: CI Actions (GitHub/GitLab/Gitea) deferred -- each platform needs a wrapper around just lint-commits with platform-specific branch semantics." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
